  "body": "As a user\r\nI want to retrieve more than 24 hours of data\r\nSo that if I am offline for the weekend I will still be able to read old messages\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWe want to allow the user to retrieve more days of history without having to manually hit the gaps buttons.\r\nThe issue is that syncing is already fairly slow on 24 hours, so we need to strike a balance between fetching too much data and have slow syncing times, or fetch too little and miss messages.\r\nTherefore we need to find a solution, and we need to see how much we can afford, ideally 7 days would be best, but that might not be possible.\r\n\r\nA few ideas is to for example don't sync public chats for 24 days, but sync only one-to-one topics, which are the most relevant.\r\nOr sync only up to X messages, but that might be tricky as we don't know how many messages are shown to the user until received.\r\n\r\nSolutions might include some UX to reduce the impact on syncing cc @errorists ",
